   ---

   This repository ports rule logic from the proprietary GRL OntOLinter
   (https://www.graphresearchlabs.com/ontolinter), released here under
   Apache 2.0 with permission, deliberately limited to six rules so
   the workshop linter remains a teaching tool rather than a competing
   product. The full OntOLinter rule library remains proprietary.

   The Cross-Border Payments and AML Ontology (CBPA) example files
   in examples/cbpa/ are released under CC-BY-SA-4.0 (matching the
   gist licence) — they are a teaching exemplar designed for the
   workshop, not a production ontology.

   N3.js (docs/lib/n3.min.js) is included under its own MIT licence;
   see https://github.com/rdfjs/N3.js for the source.
